post_text:
Cook Manager
Lyncourt UFSD is a small, low-stress, single building PreK-8 public school district seeking a qualified Cook Manager. Full-time (7 hours per day), 10-mo position with benefits, $26,600 starting salary plus part-time summer work as needed. Candidates must meet the minimum qualifications of the job title, as outlined in the Onondaga County Civil Service job description. Apply by sending your resume to: Lyncourt Union Free School District Attn: C. Marchese/Job #21-CM, 2707 Court Street, Syracuse, NY 13208 or email to cmarchese@lyncourtschool.or or online at OLAS by 6/17/2020.

Spring Specials‚Äô Spectacular!

What?

The Special area teachers would like to make a virtual presentation of projects, activities or performances that you do! You can send us a photo or video to include in our presentation. (Please be aware that we will use clips from your videos if they are longer than 10 seconds).

Who?
Students of ALL grade levels. Parents can help younger students:)

How?
Submit a photo or video to a special area teacher.

Ideas/Examples:
Photos or video clips of: art projects and/or art work, music projects, singing, practicing your instrument, cooking/baking, sewing, tech projects, reading, being active (PE), exercising, yoga, running, walking in the park... The possibilities are endless!

Deadline:
Friday, May 29th
Special Areas:
PE - Mrs. Byrne and Mr. Rehm Technology - Mrs. Derouchie Music - Mrs. Gross
Band - Mrs. Hayden
Art - Mr. Retz FACS - Mrs. Tarsel

Wednesday. Today is the day you can access your child's report card on School Tool.

If you did not receive an email from School Tool with a password, please follow these steps once you have opened up the School Tool site (There is a link on our Lyncourt Website):

Click the ‚ÄúNew User or Forgot Password?‚Äù link and type in your email address that school has on file in the Username window. Click Submit. An Email will be generated with your new password, and sent to the Email address you entered. After a few moments, your password will arrive at your registered Email account. At the SchoolTool Login page, enter your registered Email address in the Username window, and enter the new assigned password.

Visit our website for more details.

shared_text:
Kimberly Sutherland Cintron‚ÄéLyncourtPTO20/21
April 6 at 1:20 AM ¬∑

Lyncourt car parade route. Please allow 30-40 minutes per zone. Zone 1 is first, 2 is 2nd and 3rd. So we will be leaving at 11:05-11:10. Sadly there are a couple of streets I couldn't plan logistically and cross streets are a good way for you to see us. Keep your social distance. Some cross streets only have 2 or 3 houses so go to the street closest to your home. Do not interact with others please. We need all be safe!! This is something never done before so please be patient and thankful that we are able to pull this together for all of the students. I will share our path with you. Ignore the notes, those are for staff purposes.

post_text:
Here is the latest:
Phone message from superintendent Austin:

The Onondaga County Superintendents met with County Executive Ryan McMahon and County Health Commissioner Dr. Gupta earlier today to discuss COVID-19 and the potential impact on schools.

By now, you are likely all aware of the County Executive‚Äôs announcement of a State of Emergency in Onondaga County.

As per the order of the County Executive, students will be out of school beginning Monday March 23, 2020. Students are scheduled to return on Tuesday, April 14th.

The district plans to share more information tomorrow regarding this announcement. As we prepare for continuity of instruction for all of our students we anticipate using next week to solidify plans to meet the needs of our students.

We recognize that some of you may be uncomfortable sending your children to school. Please know that we respect your right as parents to choose what is best for your child.

Thank you.... please remember information is changing quickly. Please stay tuned.
We appreciate your understanding.

Games are played every Saturday morning at Sunnycrest Park (Henninger High School) between the hours of 9am and Noon.

post_text:
News from PreK:
Last week our UPK classrooms were visited by Mr. Doug, a mail carrier in the United States Postal Service as an extension to their learning in the CKLA Families and Communities. He shared with the students his love for his job explaining that he helps others get special packages, birthday cards, and letters from loved ones. He also showed us the various hats he uses when delivering mail on his route (and some that he borrowed from his younger daughter). He may have just inspired some of our children to become mail carriers in the future. One parent messaged that her son said, "it was the best day ever because a mailman came to school today!''

Our Pajama Drive hosted by UPK is coming to an end. Friday, December 6th is the last day to bring in a new pair of pajamas to be donated to children in need with the help of Scholastic Books.

Children who donated a pair of pajamas can wear their pajamas to school this Friday. If you were unable to donate a pair of pajamas, but still want your child to be able to wear his/her pajamas. they can if they bring in a dollar. The money collected will be pooled together to purchase additional pajamas to be included in our donation.

Any questions, please email Mrs. Pyland at lpyland@lyncourtschool.org.

News from Mrs. Pyland (UPK teacher):

This month in our classroom, we have had an optometrist's office in our dramatic play area and today, we were visited by Ryan and Kate from Eyecare of CNY to enhance our understanding of optometry. They shared with us how they test for color blindness, how they help pick the right prescription for someone's lenses or contacts, and they even visited our Lyncourt Optometrist Office!
